<p>For some reason, I can't loop and mute a simple youtube video. I've put all the necessaries attributes and used the js available here <a href="https://developers.google.com/youtube/iframe_api_reference#Examples" rel="nofollow">https://developers.google.com/youtube/iframe_api_reference#Examples</a> but nothing seems to work</p>  <pre><code>&lt;iframe id="player" type="text/html" style="width:500px;height:400px;" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/bXpUFEWmD6c?autoplay=1&amp;rel=0?loop=1&amp;showinfo=0&amp;html5=1&amp;autoplay=1&amp;autohide=0&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;hd=1&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;disablekb=1&amp;rel=0&amp;enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;  function onYouTubeIframeAPIReady() {   var player;   player = new YT.Player('player', {    playerVars: { 'loop': 1,  },     events: {       'onReady': onPlayerReady,       'onPlaybackQualityChange': onPlayerPlaybackQualityChange,       'onStateChange': onPlayerStateChange,       'onError': onPlayerError     }   }); }  function onPlayerReady(event) {   event.target.setVolume(0);   event.target.playVideo(); } </code></pre>